I upgraded to EIDE, it cost me around US$ 70.
hdparm 2.1 tells me I have transfer rates around 2.5 Mb/s, which I'm
quite happy with (this is under linux, I haven't tested under DOS,
and Windows dosn't work at all..)

Going to SCSI would mean that I'd have to buy a card that's more expensive,
I would need to replace my old disks, which still costs money, though it's
getting pretty cheap, and that I probably would need a serial/parallell
card (which is onboard the EIDE controller)

For the price, I think EIDE is the way to go, at least if you have
IDE already.

Just IMHO, and for the record,
I'm no relation to any SCSI or (E)IDE disks or controllers.

